00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,285
Groupby is one of my favorite functions in pandas.

2
00:00:03,285 --> 00:00:06,180
It lets you group your data and aggregate information about

3
00:00:06,180 --> 00:00:10,350
those groups or perform group-specific transformations.

4
00:00:10,350 --> 00:00:13,380
In this section, we'll focus on using groupby

5
00:00:13,380 --> 00:00:16,410
to get summary statistics about different groups of data.

6
00:00:16,410 --> 00:00:21,250
This notebook I read in the CSV for census income data.

7
00:00:21,770 --> 00:00:25,335
Previously, we learned that we can get summary statistics

8
00:00:25,335 --> 00:00:28,860
on the whole dataset with functions like describe and mean.

9
00:00:28,860 --> 00:00:32,415
From this, I can find the mean of the whole dataset.

10
00:00:32,415 --> 00:00:36,285
But what if I wanted to find the mean for each work class in the data?

11
00:00:36,285 --> 00:00:41,110
You can use the groupby function combined with a mean function to do this.

12
00:00:41,110 --> 00:00:43,100
We can even split the data by

13
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:47,375
multiple columns by using a list of the columns we want to group by.

14
00:00:47,375 --> 00:00:54,125
Here we are grouping by work class and race to visualize how groups have different means.

15
00:00:54,125 --> 00:00:57,890
If we want to keep the columns we grouped by in the DataFrame,

16
00:00:57,890 --> 00:01:02,510
we can specify the as index parameter to false.

17
00:01:02,510 --> 00:01:05,330
In this example, we are keeping the columns and only

18
00:01:05,330 --> 00:01:09,310
selecting the capital gains to derive the mean values from each group.

19
